<title>JAPAN: Forex volatilty makes policy hard - Japan MOF quoted.</title>
<headline>Forex volatilty makes policy hard - Japan MOF quoted.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-05-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>Volatility in foreign exchange rates makes it difficult to execute stable economic policy, Jiji news agency quoted Japanese Finance Minister Hiroshi Mitsuzuka as saying on Tuesday.  </p>
<p>&quot;Extreme movements up or down in foreign exchange rates make it very difficult to execute stable economic policy,&quot; Jiji quoted Mitsuzuka as telling a parliamentary panel.</p>
